<HL>
   Swiss Jobless Rate Eases to 0.5%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   EUROP
</CO>
<LP>
   BERN -- Switzerland's unemployment rate eased to 0.5% in
April from 0.6% in March, the government said. Persons out of
work numbered 16,634 in April, while 18,701 jobs went
unfilled.
   In April 1989, the jobless rates was 0.6%.
</LP>
