<HL>
   Hong Kong Orders Fall 2%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A7D
</SO>
<CO>
   FREST
</CO>
<LP>
   HONG KONG -- Orders on hand at Hong Kong's 200 largest
manufacturers fell 2% in March from a year earlier and was
unchanged compared with the previous month, the government
reported.
   The backlog of orders in the clothing sector, Hong Kong's
largest export industry, was also off 2% from the previous
year and unchanged from February.
</LP>
