<HL>
   Carter Holt to Buy
   Brierley's 50% Stake
   In Jointly Owned Firm
   ----
   Special to The Wall Street Journal
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6B
</SO>
<CO>
   C.CHH A.BRY
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   AUCKLAND, New Zealand -- Carter Holt Harvey Ltd. said it
is buying Brierley Investments Ltd.'s 50% stake in their
joint-venture packaging concern Printpac-UEB for 110 million
New Zealand dollars (US$63.1 million).
   The New Zealand timber, building materials and packaging
concern said the purchase price will include NZ$30.5 million
and an issue of 30 million Carter Holt shares valued at
NZ$2.65 each.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   The purchase, which would be retroactive to April 1, is
subject to approval by New Zealand's antitrust regulators,
Carter Holt said.
   Carter Holt and Brierley formed Printpac-UEB in 1989 as a
vehicle to buy UEB Packaging Ltd.
   Richard Carter, executive chairman of Carter Holt, said
that following the purchase of UEB Packaging last year, the
joint venture "is now a large, finely focussed and mature"
organization. "It is, therefore, now more appropriately
designed to operate under a single ownership structure," Mr.
Carter said.
   Bruce Hancox, chairman of Brierley Investments, said his
company is satisfied with its investment in Carter Holt
through the share issue.
</TEXT>
