<HL>
   Business Brief -- Guilford Mills Inc.:
   Posner of Graniteville Co.
   Increases Holding to 10.3%
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   GFD
</CO>
<IN>
TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)
</IN>
<LP>
   Investor Victor Posner said Guilford Mills Inc. is seeking
talks in connection with a possible business combination
between Guilford, Greensboro, S.C., and closely held
Graniteville Co., Graniteville, S.C. Mr. Posner is chairman
of Graniteville.
   Charles Hayes, Guilford chairman and chief executive
officer, said his company is interested in acquiring
Graniteville for either cash or stock. He said he contacted
Mr. Posner about two weeks ago.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Mr. Hayes said the two companies would make a good
combination, as both specialize in manufacturing clothes for
the career apparel market. In fiscal 1989, Guilford earned
$26 million, or $2.67 a share, on revenue of about $620
million.
   In a filing with the Securities and Exchange Commission,
Mr. Posner said he raised his stake in Guilford to 10.3%
after buying 20,000 shares on May 3 for $22 a share and
88,100 shares for $20.625 a share.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
