   Marketing Brief -- Cablevision Systems Corp.:
   Cable Operator Posts Loss
   Of $74 Million for Quarter
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   CVC
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Cablevision Systems Corp. said it had a net loss of $74
million, or $3.38 a share, for the first quarter, citing
additional interest, depreciation and amortization expenses
related to 1989 acquisitions.
   A year earlier, the Woodbury, N.Y., cable-television
company had a net loss of $59.1 million, or $2.73 a share.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Revenues rose 21% to $133.8 million from $110.7 million.
   Cablevision said operating profit before depreciation and
amortization rose 19% to $54 million. Net interest expense
rose $17 million to $64 million, while depreciation and
amortization expense rose $10 million to about $54 million.
   At March 31, Cablevision had 1.3 million subscribers in 11
states, as well as interests in programming and advertising
sales companies.
