<HL>
   REVIEW &amp; OUTLOOK (Editorial) -- Asides:
   Accounting for Congress?
</HL>
<DATE>
05/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A12
</SO>
<GV>
COMMERCE DEPARTMENT (COM)
CONGRESS (CNG)
</GV>
<LP>
   The Census Bureau can't explain the low rate of census
forms that have been filled out and returned; it's about 75%
nationwide, down from nearly 90% a decade ago. Some say it's
apathy, but we say it was a marketing error. The Census
Bureau warned in grave tones that if people failed to return
their forms, they could lose congressional representation.
What a brier patch. The prospect of fewer congressional seats
might seem like an even better alternative than the proposed
12-year-term limitation for Congressmen.
</LP>
<TEXT>
</TEXT>
